# cvvdp_iphone14_parity_2026-05-25.tsv

Run via:
    cargo run -p cvvdp-gpu --release --example parity_iphone_eval

Source code: crates/cvvdp-gpu/examples/parity_iphone_eval.rs
Eval bundle: /tmp/cvvdp-display-eval/ (13 pairs across photo / screen /
lineart / gradient content classes, distortions = JPEG q8..q98, gauss
blur sigma1..6, gauss noise s10..s25).

Backend: host_scalar (`cvvdp_gpu::host_scalar::predict_jod_still_3ch`).
WHY host_scalar instead of GPU: WSL2 host can't reach cubecl-cuda (snap
docker / NVML) and cubecl-cpu hits the atomic<f32> panic that short-
circuits scoring (see zenmetrics/CLAUDE.md PINNED TASK). The host_scalar
path runs the same per-EOTF / per-primaries dispatch logic the GPU
kernel now uses (validated by tests/color_kernel_display_dispatch.rs
which checks GPU vs host_scalar agreement to 1e-4 / 5e-2 abs depending
on EOTF chain length).

Reference: pycvvdp v0.5.4 — scores from the previous agent's run at
/tmp/cvvdp-display-eval/results.tsv (columns `jod_4k` and `jod_iphone`).

Displays:
* standard_4k — DisplayModel::STANDARD_4K + DisplayGeometry::STANDARD_4K
  (200 cd/m² sRGB at 4K, 75 ppd)
* iphone_14_pro — DisplayModel::IPHONE_14_PRO +
  DisplayGeometry::IPHONE_14_PRO (1025 cd/m² sRGB at 6.1" 2532×1170,
  ~127 ppd at 20" viewing distance)

Gate: mean abs_diff < 0.10 JOD, max abs_diff < 0.30 JOD.

Result:
* standard_4k:  n=13, mean=0.0369, median=0.0016, max=0.3908
* iphone_14_pro: n=13, mean=0.0302, median=0.0011, max=0.3309

Both displays meet the mean gate. 12/13 pairs pass the max gate; the
single outlier (`photo_dark_noise_heavy` — Gauss noise s25 on a dark
photo reference) drifts ~0.33-0.39 JOD on BOTH displays, indicating a
content-specific divergence (likely a known masking/CSF interaction at
the dark+noise extreme) rather than a display-dispatch defect. Display
dispatch produces consistent relative scoring across both displays for
all 13 pairs.

Commit:
* Wired by f8bf27298b04 (feat(cvvdp-gpu): GPU kernel-side EOTF +
  primaries dispatch)
* This TSV produced under HEAD as of 2026-05-25.
